thought:
**Analyzing the Administrative Restructuring of "Xã Cát Quế"**

Okay, so I'm tasked with pinpointing the new administrative unit for the old address "Xã Cát Quế, Huyện Hoài Đức, Thành phố Hà Nội". This means I need to sift through the available resolutions and the list of new wards.

First, I identified the key pieces: "Xã Cát Quế" is the old ward, and "Thành phố Hà Nội" is the province. The district "Huyện Hoài Đức" is also important for context, as it's part of the address.  I immediately consulted the provincial resolutions (60-NQ/TW) to make sure there wasn't a province name change, but "Thành phố Hà Nội" remains unchanged. Good.

Now, the crucial step: I dove into the relevant resolutions specifically concerning "Thành phố Hà Nội". Resolution 1656/NQ-UBTVQH15, "Sắp xếp các đơn vị hành chính cấp xã của thành phố Hà Nội", is the one.  Scanning through, I zeroed in on the lines mentioning "Xã Cát Quế".  Bingo!  Line 103 explicitly states: "Sắp xếp toàn bộ diện tích tự nhiên, quy mô dân số của các xã Cát Quế, Dương Liễu, Đắc Sở, Minh Khai và Yên Sở thành xã mới có tên gọi là **xã Dương Hòa**."

To confirm, I double-checked the "New wards" list, and there it is: `{"ward_code":"09856","ward_name":"Xã Dương Hòa","province_name":"Thành phố Hà Nội"}`.  Perfect match!

My confidence level is high because "Xã Cát Quế" is directly cited as being merged into "xã Dương Hòa". The JSON output will be straightforward: I'll cite Resolution 1656/NQ-UBTVQH15 with the relevant line (103), mark the confidence as "high", and provide "Thành phố Hà Nội" as the province, "09856" as the ward code, and "Xã Dương Hòa" as the new ward name.

I meticulously re-checked the resolution for any other mentions of "Xã Cát Quế" or "Hoài Đức". Line 30 and line 102 were flagged in my scan, both mentioning Hoài Đức, but they refer to other newly formed wards, specifically "xã Hoài Đức", not including "Xã Cát Quế". "Xã Cát Quế" is unambiguously assigned to "xã Dương Hòa." This mapping is definitive.
